Test: Horizontal Text Alignment

        /* Reset for consistency */
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; }

        /* Test container */
        .test-container {
            width: 600px;
            height: 500px;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        /* Test-specific CSS */
        .box {
            width: 300px;
            height: 80px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #666;
            background-color: white;
            line-height: 1.2;
        }

        .align-left {
            text-align: left;
            background-color: #ffcccc;
        }

        .align-center {
            text-align: center;
            background-color: #ccffcc;
        }

        .align-right {
            text-align: right;
            background-color: #ccccff;
        }

        .align-justify {
            text-align: justify;
            background-color: #ffffcc;
        }

        .align-start {
            text-align: start;
            background-color: #ffccff;
        }

        .align-end {
            text-align: end;
            background-color: #ccffff;
        }





            Left: This text is aligned to the left side of the container.


            Center: This text is centered within the container.


            Right: This text is aligned to the right side of the container.


            Justify: This text is justified to fill the entire width of the container with even spacing.


            Start: This text uses logical start alignment.


            End: This text uses logical end alignment.





